# Components

Prefer:

- Server Components

Use Client Components only when necessary.

# Forms

Always use:

- React Hook Form
- Zod validation

Never use useState for large forms.

# Tables

- Use reusable table components
- Support loading states
- Support empty states
- Support error states

# Accessibility

Always:

- Label inputs
- Use semantic HTML
- Support keyboard navigation and focus trapping inside active modals/drawers
- Provide explicit aria attributes (e.g. `aria-expanded`, `aria-label`, `aria-controls`) for interactive toggle components
- Enforce highly visible focus states (`focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[#fc661e]`) for all keyboard navigators
- Adhere strictly to WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios

# Styling & Responsiveness (Official Government Portal Standards)

Use:

- Tailwind utilities
- Design system tokens
- Fluid responsive layouts to ensure seamless rendering across:
  - Mobile screens (320px+) with no horizontal scroll breaks
  - Standard/older government office monitors (1024x768, 1280x1024 resolutions)
  - Desktop widescreen monitors and Macs (1440x900, 1920x1080, and high-res Retina displays)
- Dynamic content adapters for mobile layout safety:
  - `flex-shrink-0` on critical items (dates, icons, badges) to prevent text squeezing/collisions
  - Swapping detailed layout blocks (like full date strings) with compact formats on small viewports
- Clean institutional styling with official state emblem integration, bilingual language support (English/Hindi), and prominent helpdesk links.

Avoid:

- Inline styles
- Magic numbers
- Hardcoded colors
- Fixed element widths that cause horizontal scrolling on smaller screens or visual breaking on low-res screens

# Testing

For business logic:

- Write unit tests

For API integrations:

- Write integration tests

For critical user journeys:

- Write E2E tests

Always test:

- Validation
- Permissions
- Data transformations
- Complex calculations

Do not write tests for:
- Simple presentational components
- Third-party libraries
- Framework behavior